original: Hultgren, Folke Birger, kyrkoherde, Hult, f. 29/5/08 i Eksjö. G. 36 m. Elna Rylander. Barn: Berit f. 38, Margareta 42, Karin 44. — Stud:ex. i Eksjö 27, teol. fil. ex. 28, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Linköp. stift 33. Kommin. i Hycklinge 36, kyrkoh. i Hult o. Edshult sed. 42. Var i Hycklinge ordf. i kyrkostämma, är i Hult o. Edshult ordf. i kyrkostämman o. past :stämman, Hults skolstyr. o. barnav:nd samt Edshults skolstyr.
translated: Hultgren, Folke Birger, parish priest, Hult, born on May 29th, 1908 in Eksjö. Married in 1936 to Elna Rylander. They had three children: Berit, born in 1938, Margareta, born in 1942, and Karin, born in 1944. He completed his high school education in Eksjö in 1927, achieved his theology degree in 1928, passed his practical theology exams and was ordained as a priest for the Linköping Diocese in 1933. He was a curate in Hycklinge from 1936 and became the parish priest in Hult and Edshult in 1942. He was chairman of the church meeting in Hycklinge and is chairman of the church meeting and parish council, Hult's school board, child welfare committee, and Edshult's school board.
